[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and consent, longitudinal-store initialization with open-item seeding, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-context loading with multi-system retrieval, conversation handling with tool-use orchestration, output safety screening with citation verification, action execution with idempotent multi-system writes, warm-handoff routing to human case managers, and audit logging with care-coordination-specific telemetry. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (multi-system integration as architectural primitive, persistent open-item state with care-team ownership, proactive outreach scheduler with tempo discipline, care-management workforce integration, and patient-segment-aware response calibration).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CONSENT ──────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via care team, payer care-management   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    program, or self-enrollment through institutional      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    portal]                                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to care-coordination AI  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      interaction with case-management-leadership and      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      legal-counsel-reviewed language                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Explicit non-clinician disclosure acknowledged       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-system-data-access consent collected (chart    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      access, eligibility access, pharmacy access,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      scheduling access, social-services access; each      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      separately revocable where appropriate)              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Channel-preference and quiet-hours capture           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Privacy posture explained in plain language          │
