[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Scope discipline]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Within-scope: open-item tracking and surfacing,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      appointment scheduling and rescheduling, referral    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tracking, lab and imaging completion tracking,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      eligibility and benefits explanation, prior-auth     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      status tracking, refill coordination, transition-of- │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care coordination, SDoH screening and routing,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care-team-message facilitation, emergency screening, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      patient-preference capture, longitudinal continuity  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Outside-scope (route appropriately): clinical        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      decision-making, treatment adjustment, diagnosis,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      medication dose changes, controlled-substance        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handling, prior-auth appeal preparation, complex     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      benefits disputes, complex SDoH crisis intervention, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      mental-health crisis (route to mental-health bot or  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      crisis pathway), social-services eligibility         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      determination, content the patient's clinician       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      should address, emergency clinical situations        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Citation discipline]                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Every patient-facing claim about a system-of-record  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      fact (appointment, referral, lab, medication,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      benefit, eligibility, prior auth) is grounded in a   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      retrieved record from the system of record           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Source identifier preserved in audit trail           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tone discipline]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Warm and patient, calibrated to patient segment      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Avoids surveillance flavor in proactive outreach     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Avoids companion-pattern simulation                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Avoids paternalism                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Plain language at the patient's stated reading level │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: composed response with citations and tool-call │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    audit trail]                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
