[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration as architectural primitive.** Each integration (EHR, scheduling, referral, eligibility, pharmacy, care-management, social-services) is a contract. Contracts are versioned, monitored, and governed by integration ownership. The bot does not invent system facts; the bot reads from and writes to the systems with explicit, audited tool calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Persistent open-item state with care-team ownership.** The open coordination items per patient are durable, viewable by patient and care team, and editable by care team. The bot reads, proposes, and updates; the source of truth is the open-item store and the underlying systems of record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Proactive outreach scheduler with tempo discipline.** The bot's outreach is scheduled, tempo-disciplined, channel-appropriate, and quiet-hours-respectful. Per-cohort tempo policies are reviewed by patient-experience leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Patient-segment-aware calibration.** The bot's tone, pacing, vocabulary, escalation thresholds, and tool-use depth are calibrated per patient segment. The segment-classification logic is reviewed by clinical and care-management leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-management workforce integration.** The bot is part of the case-management workflow, not a parallel product. Case-manager-facing dashboards show what the bot is doing for their patients; case-manager feedback influences bot behavior; case-manager-flagged outreach is honored.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Idempotent multi-system writes.** Every write carries an idempotency key. Race conditions, retries, and duplicate-action prevention are addressed at the integration layer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every system-of-record claim is grounded in a retrieved record with source preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When uncertain, the bot routes to a human. When the patient's situation is ambiguous, the bot asks rather than assumes. When the bot's tools are degraded, the bot acknowledges the degradation rather than making things up.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Open-item closure rate, referral-completion rate, scheduling success rate, prior-auth-resolution rate, escalation completion rate, and patient-experience scores vary by cohort. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical, operational, and patient-experience leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any upstream system is unavailable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble reaching that system right now; let me connect you with a person who can help" with direct routing to the case manager. Graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
